      <div align="Left">
<!---------------------------->
<table cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Recommended Level<br>for starting quest:</b></td><td valign="bottom"> 5<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting zone:</b></td><td valign="top"> Neriak - Third Gate (Dark Elf only)<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Additional zones:</b></td><td valign="top"> Neriak - Commons, Nektulos Forest<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting NPC:</b></td><td valign="top"> Ulraz S`Lon<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Reward:</b></td><td valign="top"> Bone Hilted Long Sword<br><br></td></tr>
</table>

LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP  <br>
Damage: 5<br>
Delay: 30 <br>
Ratio: 6<br>
Str: +1 Int: +1  <br>
Weight: 8.5 <br>
Weapon Skill: One Hand Slash <br>
Classes: Warrior Rogue Bard Paladin Ranger  <br>
Races: All Races  <br>
Inventory Slot: Either Melee <br>
<br>
Ulraz S`Lon is in the Lodge of the Dead, Neriak 3rd Quarter.  He is a Shadow Knight trainer on the first floor.<br>
<br>
You say, 'Hail, Ulraz S`Lon' <br>
<br>
Ulraz S`Lon says 'So you are the next pathetic maggot I have the displeasure of training to be a useful Shadowknight of the Lodge of the Dead. First you must get yourself outfitted in a suit of [armor], those rags you wear can not even contain the stench of your miserable hide and will do no good protecting it from the edge of an enemies blade. ' <br>
<br>
You say, 'what armor?' <br>
<br>
Ulraz S`Lon says 'Seek Krivn S'Tai in the Commoner quarter of Neriak and give him this request parchment. Krivn S'Tai has been paid in advance by the Lodge of the Dead for the requested service. Simply give him the request parchment and he will instruct you further. When you have outfitted yourself in a suit of armor return to the Lodge of the Dead and I will grant you [another task].' <br>
<br>
After you have completed the set of armor (or before hand if you like, just make sure you have started the armor part.  You may then return to Ulraz S'Lon.<br>
You say, 'I am ready for another task'<br>
<br>
Ulraz S`Lon says 'Ah, you are eager to advance further within the Lodge of the Dead. Although it is my duty to aid your training, do not allow your arrogance to blind you to your lowly position amongst the Queens most loyal subjects. Your next task is to assist the construction of a [weapon] and [shield] worthy of being wielded by a Shadowknight of the Lodge of the Dead.' <br>
<br>
You say, 'what weapon?' <br>
<br>
Ulraz S`Lon says 'Beyond the mouth of Neriak lies the Nektulos Forest. There the walking dead can be found digging their way from the ashen soil of the [Ultricle], their flesh cured and hardened and bones strengthened from the minerals and volcanic ash in which they rested in death. Return some of these undead to the rest they have abandoned and bring to me some Leathered Zombie Flesh, a Petrified Humerus bone, and a Petrified Rib bone. '<br>
<br>
By all reports, petrified Humerous and Rib bones are very rare. Your best bet on getting petrified bones is at the 'Counsilman' camp around 2000, 1200 in Nektulos Forest.  The zombie flesh can be found from the zombies that sometimes appear with the skeletons.<br>
<br>
In return for these three items, you will receive a rounded sword blade and a bone hilt.  <b>Your next step is to sharpen this blade.</b>  Purchase a sharpening stone (or several) from various smithing vendors.  Place the rounded blade and the sharpening stone (no water flask necessary) into a forge and press combine.  This combine is trivial at 21.  If you fail, the blade will be returned to you as it was, and the stone will be lost.  If you succeed, you will receive the sharpened version of the blade.<br>
<br>
Take the hilt and the sharpened blade to Opal H'rugal and hand her both items.  She will then give you your weapon.<Br>
<br>

